The reversed linked list should have the same number of nodes as the original linked list.
The last node of the original linked list should become the first node of the reversed linked list.
The first node of the original linked list should become the last node of the reversed linked list.
The order of the nodes in the reversed linked list should be reversed compared to the original linked list.
The `next` pointer of the last node in the reversed linked list should be null.
The `next` pointer of the first node in the reversed linked list should point to the second node in the original linked list.
The `next` pointer of each node in the reversed linked list should point to the previous node in the original linked list.
